THE FULL AXE-PERIENCE!
Birthday? Bach? Team Building? Other Bad-Axe Event?
Looking to host your private event with axe throwing style? We have plenty of space to host your event of up to 33 people.Â  Click
here
to book your private event and donâ€™t forget about the special pricing for non-peak hours!Â  We are your go-to for employee appreciation, holiday parties, networking events, birthdays, graduations, customer appreciation events and anything in between that needs a little AXEcitement!
Have more than that? We can bring the party to you with our
mobile unit
.Â  Start gathering your co-workers, your friends, or your family. We guarantee youâ€™ll all have a kick-axe time with our coaching axe-perts guiding you along the way!
PRIVATE EVENTS:
We would LOVE to host your private event at Axe Hole NPR for birthdays, team building or any other reason to gather a group of people!Â  We can host a maximum of 32 guests with our team ready to show your party a safe and fun experience!Â  You are welcome to cater in any outside food you would like, but no outside beverages are allowed.
Non-Peak Hours: Available
as low as $500
for 2-hour event

Standard Rate for 2 hours of $45/person (for 20+ throwers)
What are Non-Peak Hours?
Hours we are not typically open (ex: Wednesday evening, ending before 5p on a Friday)
Hours that tend to have less reservation demand, such as early in the day on a Saturday or Sunday.
Friday & Saturday evenings are always peak, holidays and special downtown events may fall into peak hours as well.
Scroll to the bottom of this page for a link to search and book directly for your private party during non-peak hours!
E-mail us (info@axeholenpr.com) or call us (727-271-2863) to discuss peak hours availability.
Book Now
Common Party Related Questions:
You are welcome to bring in food, birthday cake, etc for your party.
We are unable to allow outside beverages.
Itâ€™s a surprise party â€“ what about the guest of honorâ€™s waiver?Â  Itâ€™s okay!Â  They can sign after you arrive.

Do I have to pay for people that are not throwing?Â  Absolutely not, they are welcome to hang out in the bar and lounge area for the party where they can watch the throwing action!Â  Book your reservation for just the number of throwers you will have.
